				<h1>Assistive Care services</h1>

				<h2>Helping you live independently at home</h2>
				<!--#include virtual="/includes/virginia-story.inc"-->
				<p><span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> Assistive Care services provide non-medical assistance with <a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#ADL">activities of daily living</a> for adults and seniors when a health issue has made it difficult to manage everyday tasks on their own. These services are provided primarily by <a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#HHA">home health aides</a> on an ongoing shift (two-hour or more) basis, and are available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. This care is also sometimes referred to as personal care or aide services.</p>

				<h2>Assistive care specialists and services</h2>

				<p>Our <a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#CaregiversProfessional">care professionals</a> excel at what they do, and their assistance can help adults and seniors continue living independently at home—where they want to be. Our <a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#AssistiveCare">assistive care</a> specialists include <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> Home Health Aides, Certified Nursing Assistants, <a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#HomemakerService">Homemakers</a>, and Companions. Whether occasional services or <a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#Live-inCare">live-in</a> care is needed, we match the client’s needs with the right <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> professional.</p>

				<h2>Self-care assistance with activities of daily living</h2>

					<ul>
						<li>Dressing and grooming</li>
						<li>Bathing and toileting</li>
						<li>Walking, moving, and transferring (including safe use of wheelchairs, walkers, or lifts)</li>
						<li>Basic exercise</li>
						<li>Reminders about medications and appointments</li>
						<li>Meal preparation, help with eating, and nutritious food selection</li>
	            			</ul><br>

	            		<h2>Household support services</h2>

	            			<ul>
				                <li>Light housekeeping, such as vacuuming, dusting, and sweeping</li>
				                <li>Washing and folding laundry</li>
				                <li>Trash removal</li>
				                <li>Shopping for groceries, picking up prescriptions, and other errands</li>
				                <li>Companionship (such as conversation, reading, and on outings)</li>
	            			</ul><br>

	            		<h2>Quality care you can trust</h2>
	            		<p><span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> takes extra steps to ensure clinical excellence and safety: </p>
		            		<ul>
				                <li><span class="bold">Rigorous hiring standards.</span>All <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> health care professionals undergo an in-depth interview process, with thorough background checks and work history verification.</li>
				                <li><span class="bold">Ongoing supervision and training.</span> All aspects of your care plan are overseen by a clinical manager who is a registered nurse and makes routine supervisory visits. We assess your care team's skills on a regular basis and provide ongoing training and education.</li>
				                <li><span class="bold">Client and family-centered team approach.</span> Our <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> caregivers partner with you in your care. We communicate regularly with you, your family caregivers, your physician, and your care team.</li>
				                <li><span class="bold">Commitment to our core values.</span> All of our health care professionals are committed to providing care with compassion, excellence, and reliability &mdash; it's <span class="italics"><a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#BayadaWay">The <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> Way</a></span></li>
		            		</ul>

		        <!-- definitions (hidden) -->
			<div id="ADL" class="define-word"><p>Activities of daily living refer to an individual's daily habits. ADLs are often used to help determine an individual's ability to function at home or another less-restricted environment of care. Examples of ADLs include bathing, dressing, eating, moving around, using the bathroom, and walking.</p></div>

			<div id="HHA" class="define-word"><p>A HHA is a nurse aide who has been tested and proven competent in home health skills. Home Health Aides are able to work in the private home.</p></div>

			<div id="CaregiversProfessional" class="define-word"><p><span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> employees who provide care to our clients are referred to as <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> caregivers, care professionals, or health care professionals. To distinguish from family caregivers, we include <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> in front of the word caregiver when referring to our employees who are providing care to a client.</p></div>

			<div id="AssistiveCare" class="define-word"><p>The assistive care practice is the first specialty practice of <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> Home Health Care. Its services include assistance with activities of daily living (ADL) and household support services for adults and seniors. <a href="glossary-a.asp#AssistiveCare" target="_blank">Read full assistive care definition...</a></p></div>

			<div id="HomemakerService" class="define-word"><p>A person who performs general household duties such as cooking, cleaning, child care, and shopping for a client unable to perform these tasks themselves. A homemaker is not a trained provider of personal care.</p></div>

			<div id="Live-inCare" class="define-word"><p>Care provided by a non-relative living in the client or patient’s home.</p></div>

			<div id="BayadaWay" class="define-word"><p>Our company philosophy, <span class="italics">The <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> Way</span> expresses the values and beliefs that have been the foundation of our work since 1975. The words of The <span class='uppercase'>Bayada</span> Way come directly from our clients and their families, and our employees. We believe that our clients come first and our employees are our greatest asset.</p></div>
